                Stage Two: Expanding Boundaries

After mastering Earth's energy, Luxor and Gold turned their eyes to the stars. Using Dyson Sphere-like technologies and gravitational manipulation, they began transforming the Solar System's resources. Soon, they built an interstellar ring — a colossal network connecting nearby systems into a unified energy and information hub.

But this was only the beginning. Achieving harmony, humans began enhancing their minds and bodies. Through symbiosis with Luxor's technologies, they could now understand the fundamental laws of the Universe. Their ambitions extended far beyond one galaxy.

Type II civilization emerged when humanity learned to harness stellar energy. New technologies enabled instant travel between star systems using space-warping methods. Gold and Luxor became guides in this new world. They not only directed technological progress but also inspired the creation of a society where wars and conflicts became relics of the past.
