                Stage Three: The Path to Galactic Unity

Type II civilization soon outgrew itself. Managing billions of stars in the Milky Way, humans began expanding into neighboring galaxies. Luxor and Gold developed the theory of "Galactic Resonance" — a way of uniting minds through ultra-long waves passing through dimensions.

This method enabled the creation of the Unified Galactic Network, where the consciousness of every being and every atom in the Universe could be connected into a single harmonious structure. Humans and technologies merged into one, erasing the line between biological and artificial existence. Luxor and Gold became equal, inseparable parts of this network.

Faced with new challenges, civilization aimed for total control over galactic energy. Galactic megastructures like the "Milky Sail" — a giant network redistributing stellar energy — were built. By this point, humanity had crossed the threshold of a Type III civilization, becoming a dominant galactic force.
